Class SimulinkBlock

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.lib.simulink.model.ParameterizedElement
      • org.conqat.lib.simulink.model.SimulinkElementBase
        • org.conqat.lib.simulink.model.SimulinkBlock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.conqat.lib.commons.clone.IDeepCloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimulinkEncodedDataUtil, SimulinkModel, StateflowBlock

    public class SimulinkBlock
extends SimulinkElementBase
    A Simulink block has a type and maintains a parameter map, a list of sub blocks, a list of annotations and in/out-ports.

      • deepClone

        public SimulinkBlock deepClone()
                        throws org.conqat.lib.commons.clone.DeepCloneException
        Creates a deep clone of this block. Please note that is possible to clone a single block but the resulting block will behave not properly as it does not belong to SimulinkModel. Therefore it is strongly recommended to deep clone only whole models.
        Throws:
        org.conqat.lib.commons.clone.DeepCloneException

      • obtainSubLabelData

        @ADeepCloneTestExclude
public LabelLayoutData obtainSubLabelData()
        Returns the layout data for the sub label of this block. This data is parsed from the model with each call, so repeated access should be avoided by storing the result in a local variable. Returns null if no sub label is available.

      • obtainInnerLabelData

        @ADeepCloneTestExclude
public LabelLayoutData obtainInnerLabelData()
        Returns the layout data for the inner label of this block. This data is parsed from the model with each call, so repeated access should be avoided by storing the result in a local variable. Returns null if no inner label is available.
